  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\nG=SO(3)\\ltimes_{\\varphi} U(1).\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Composition Law.}\n\\begin{equation}\n(R,e^{i\\alpha})\\cdot(R',e^{i\\beta})\n=\n\\left(\nRR',\ne^{i\\alpha}\\varphi_R(e^{i\\beta})\n\\right).\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nIf rotation and gauge phase compose independently, the group is a direct product.  \nIf rotations act on gauge phase through an automorphism $\\varphi_R$, the coupled group is a semi-direct product:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nG=SO(3)\\ltimes_{\\varphi}U(1).\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe product law becomes:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n(R,e^{i\\alpha})\\cdot(R',e^{i\\beta})\n=\n\\left(\nRR',\ne^{i\\alpha}\\varphi_R(e^{i\\beta})\n\\right).\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nRotation and phase are treated as interacting symmetry sectors rather than merely adjacent labels.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
